Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setBufFootPrint(25.10)                                  setBufFootPrint(25.10)

Name
       setBufFootPrint - Sets the buffer cell footprint name

Syntax
        setBufFootPrint

       [-help]

       names

       [-library <libName>]

       Sets the buffer cell footprint name. This footprint name is usually as-
       signed  during  design import. The software uses buffer footprint names
       during timing optimization and top-level buffer insertion in  a  parti-
       tioned design. You can specify the library that contains the footprint.

       Use this command before running timing optimization.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation  for  each  setBufFootPrint parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

              man setBufFootPrint

       <names>
              Specifies  the buffer cell footprint name or a buffer cell name.
              When you specify a buffer cell name the Innovus  software  auto-
              matically finds the cell footprint name.

       -library <libName>
              Specifies  the  library  that contains the buffer footprint. You
              must insert a colon (:) between the library name and the  buffer
              name when you use this parameter.

Example
              * The  following  command sets the buffer cell footprint name to
                B_1P:

                setBufFootPrint B_1P

